&lt;p&gt;While fixing my &lt;a href="https://github.com/fengxia41103/jk"&gt;stock project&lt;/a&gt;, I hit a road block, that Yahoo's 
free finance API is &lt;a href="https://forums.yahoo.net/t5/Yahoo-Finance-help/Is-Yahoo-Finance-API-broken/td-p/250503"&gt;gone!&lt;/a&gt;, no more. This is quite a bummer. How
to get daily quotes so to reestablish the data stream? Well, as a the
beauty of free market, someone is always up to the service if there is
a demand. So I ended up using &lt;a href="https://www.alphavantage.co/documentation/"&gt;Alpha Advantage API&lt;/a&gt; for a change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tagging on top the &lt;a href="https://fengxia41103.github.io/myblog/data visualization.html"&gt;World Snapshot&lt;/a&gt; project, this one is
essentially a graph browser that takes the API data stream based on
user selected company symbol, and draw all the data index on a single page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://sp500chart.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com"&gt;live demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
